{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":391,"text":"We are today talking\nabout moral persuasion:"},{"time":3001,"text":"What is moral and immoral\nin trying to change people's behaviors"},{"time":7007,"text":"by using technology and using design?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9484,"text":"And I don't know what you expect,"},{"time":11340,"text":"but when I was thinking about that issue,"},{"time":13317,"text":"I early on realized what I'm not able\nto give you are answers."},{"time":17943,"text":"I'm not able to tell you\nwhat is moral or immoral,"},{"time":20738,"text":"because we're living\nin a pluralist society."},{"time":23309,"text":"My values can be radically\ndifferent from your values,"},{"time":27575,"text":"which means that what I consider\nmoral or immoral based on that"},{"time":30776,"text":"might not necessarily be\nwhat you consider moral or immoral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34769,"text":"But I also realized\nthere is one thing that I could give you,"},{"time":38007,"text":"and that is what this guy\nbehind me gave the world --"},{"time":40564,"text":"Socrates."},{"time":41738,"text":"It is questions."},{"time":43157,"text":"What I can do and what\nI would like to do with you"},{"time":45814,"text":"is give you, like that initial question,"},{"time":47783,"text":"a set of questions\nto figure out for yourselves,"},{"time":51217,"text":"layer by layer, like peeling an onion,"},{"time":54882,"text":"getting at the core of what you believe\nis moral or immoral persuasion."},{"time":60299,"text":"And I'd like to do that\nwith a couple of examples of technologies"},{"time":64364,"text":"where people have used game elements\nto get people to do things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70083,"text":"So it's at first a very simple,\nvery obvious question"},{"time":73147,"text":"I would like to give you:"},{"time":74367,"text":"What are your intentions\nif you are designing something?"},{"time":77408,"text":"And obviously, intentions\nare not the only thing,"},{"time":80805,"text":"so here is another example\nfor one of these applications."},{"time":84007,"text":"There are a couple of these kinds\nof Eco dashboards right now --"},{"time":87118,"text":"dashboards built into cars --"},{"time":88602,"text":"which try to motivate you\nto drive more fuel-efficiently."},{"time":91458,"text":"This here is Nissan's MyLeaf,"},{"time":93255,"text":"where your driving behavior\nis compared with the driving behavior"},{"time":96343,"text":"of other people,"},{"time":97518,"text":"so you can compete for who drives a route\nthe most fuel-efficiently."},{"time":100819,"text":"And these things are\nvery effective, it turns out --"},{"time":103320,"text":"so effective that they motivate people\nto engage in unsafe driving behaviors,"},{"time":107283,"text":"like not stopping at a red light,"},{"time":109069,"text":"because that way you have\nto stop and restart the engine,"},{"time":111808,"text":"and that would use quite\nsome fuel, wouldn't it?"},{"time":115078,"text":"So despite this being\na very well-intended application,"},{"time":119511,"text":"obviously there was a side effect of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121910,"text":"Here's another example\nfor one of these side effects."},{"time":124482,"text":"Commendable: a site that allows parents\nto give their kids little badges"},{"time":129290,"text":"for doing the things\nthat parents want their kids to do,"},{"time":131972,"text":"like tying their shoes."},{"time":133312,"text":"And at first that sounds very nice,"},{"time":135580,"text":"very benign, well-intended."},{"time":137754,"text":"But it turns out, if you look into\nresearch on people's mindset,"},{"time":141548,"text":"caring about outcomes,"},{"time":143059,"text":"caring about public recognition,"},{"time":144856,"text":"caring about these kinds\nof public tokens of recognition"},{"time":148741,"text":"is not necessarily very helpful"},{"time":150759,"text":"for your long-term\npsychological well-being."},{"time":153090,"text":"It's better if you care\nabout learning something."},{"time":155790,"text":"It's better when you care about yourself"},{"time":157719,"text":"than how you appear\nin front of other people."},{"time":160761,"text":"So that kind of motivational tool\nthat is used actually, in and of itself,"},{"time":165826,"text":"has a long-term side effect,"},{"time":167758,"text":"in that every time we use a technology"},{"time":169592,"text":"that uses something\nlike public recognition or status,"},{"time":172790,"text":"we're actually positively endorsing this"},{"time":175190,"text":"as a good and normal thing\nto care about --"},{"time":178624,"text":"that way, possibly having\na detrimental effect"},{"time":181512,"text":"on the long-term psychological\nwell-being of ourselves as a culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185391,"text":"So that's a second, very obvious question:"},{"time":188059,"text":"What are the effects\nof what you're doing --"},{"time":190394,"text":"the effects you're having\nwith the device, like less fuel,"},{"time":194542,"text":"as well as the effects\nof the actual tools you're using"},{"time":197271,"text":"to get people to do things --"},{"time":198969,"text":"public recognition?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200564,"text":"Now is that all -- intention, effect?"},{"time":203509,"text":"Well, there are some technologies\nwhich obviously combine both."},{"time":206667,"text":"Both good long-term and short-term effects"},{"time":209478,"text":"and a positive intention\nlike Fred Stutzman's \"Freedom,\""},{"time":212311,"text":"where the whole point\nof that application is --"},{"time":214542,"text":"well, we're usually so bombarded\nwith constant requests by other people,"},{"time":218291,"text":"with this device,"},{"time":219471,"text":"you can shut off the Internet\nconnectivity of your PC of choice"},{"time":222975,"text":"for a pre-set amount of time,"},{"time":224447,"text":"to actually get some work done."},{"time":226442,"text":"And I think most of us will agree\nthat's something well-intended,"},{"time":229617,"text":"and also has good consequences."},{"time":231861,"text":"In the words of Michel Foucault,"},{"time":233531,"text":"it is a \"technology of the self.\""},{"time":235495,"text":"It is a technology\nthat empowers the individual"},{"time":238356,"text":"to determine its own life course,"},{"time":240195,"text":"to shape itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242150,"text":"But the problem is,\nas Foucault points out,"},{"time":245158,"text":"that every technology of the self"},{"time":246967,"text":"has a technology of domination\nas its flip side."},{"time":250436,"text":"As you see in today's modern\nliberal democracies,"},{"time":255063,"text":"the society, the state,\nnot only allows us to determine our self,"},{"time":259770,"text":"to shape our self,"},{"time":260945,"text":"it also demands it of us."},{"time":262960,"text":"It demands that we optimize ourselves,"},{"time":264945,"text":"that we control ourselves,"},{"time":266809,"text":"that we self-manage continuously,"},{"time":269544,"text":"because that's the only way\nin which such a liberal society works."},{"time":273461,"text":"These technologies want us\nto stay in the game"},{"time":277753,"text":"that society has devised for us."},{"time":280550,"text":"They want us to fit in even better."},{"time":282861,"text":"They want us to optimize\nourselves to fit in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286368,"text":"Now, I don't say that\nis necessarily a bad thing;"},{"time":290033,"text":"I just think that this example\npoints us to a general realization,"},{"time":294385,"text":"and that is: no matter what technology\nor design you look at,"},{"time":298212,"text":"even something we consider\nas well-intended"},{"time":301257,"text":"and as good in its effects\nas Stutzman's Freedom,"},{"time":304247,"text":"comes with certain values embedded in it."},{"time":306978,"text":"And we can question these values."},{"time":308938,"text":"We can question: Is it a good thing"},{"time":310906,"text":"that all of us continuously\nself-optimize ourselves"},{"time":314414,"text":"to fit better into that society?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":316449,"text":"Or to give you another example:"},{"time":317965,"text":"What about a piece\nof persuasive technology"},{"time":320465,"text":"that convinces Muslim women\nto wear their headscarves?"},{"time":323680,"text":"Is that a good or a bad technology"},{"time":325756,"text":"in its intentions or in its effects?"},{"time":328343,"text":"Well, that basically depends on\nthe kind of values you bring to bear"},{"time":332621,"text":"to make these kinds of judgments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334882,"text":"So that's a third question:"},{"time":336434,"text":"What values do you use to judge?"},{"time":338588,"text":"And speaking of values:"},{"time":339953,"text":"I've noticed that in the discussion\nabout moral persuasion online"},{"time":343333,"text":"and when I'm talking with people,"},{"time":344994,"text":"more often than not,\nthere is a weird bias."},{"time":348203,"text":"And that bias is that we're asking:"},{"time":351123,"text":"Is this or that \"still\" ethical?"},{"time":353960,"text":"Is it \"still\" permissible?"},{"time":356634,"text":"We're asking things like:"},{"time":357856,"text":"Is this Oxfam donation form,"},{"time":360069,"text":"where the regular monthly\ndonation is the preset default,"},{"time":363141,"text":"and people, maybe without intending it,"},{"time":365244,"text":"are encouraged or nudged\ninto giving a regular donation"},{"time":369080,"text":"instead of a one-time donation,"},{"time":370593,"text":"is that \"still' permissible?"},{"time":371960,"text":"Is it \"still\" ethical?"},{"time":373347,"text":"We're fishing at the low end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375619,"text":"But in fact, that question,\n\"Is it 'still' ethical?\""},{"time":378117,"text":"is just one way of looking at ethics."},{"time":379922,"text":"Because if you look at the beginning\nof ethics in Western culture,"},{"time":384838,"text":"you see a very different idea\nof what ethics also could be."},{"time":388710,"text":"For Aristotle, ethics\nwas not about the question,"},{"time":392731,"text":"\"Is that still good, or is it bad?\""},{"time":395027,"text":"Ethics was about the question\nof how to live life well."},{"time":398956,"text":"And he put that in the word \"arête,\""},{"time":401161,"text":"which we, from [Ancient Greek],\ntranslate as \"virtue.\""},{"time":403940,"text":"But really, it means \"excellence.\""},{"time":405604,"text":"It means living up to your own\nfull potential as a human being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411677,"text":"And that is an idea that, I think,"},{"time":413357,"text":"Paul Richard Buchanan\nput nicely in a recent essay,"},{"time":416078,"text":"where he said,\n\"Products are vivid arguments"},{"time":418245,"text":"about how we should live our lives.\""},{"time":420826,"text":"Our designs are not ethical or unethical"},{"time":423427,"text":"in that they're using ethical\nor unethical means of persuading us."},{"time":428401,"text":"They have a moral component"},{"time":429995,"text":"just in the kind of vision\nand the aspiration of the good life"},{"time":434246,"text":"that they present to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436181,"text":"And if you look into the designed\nenvironment around us"},{"time":439708,"text":"with that kind of lens,"},{"time":440904,"text":"asking, \"What is the vision\nof the good life"},{"time":443381,"text":"that our products, our design,\npresent to us?\","},{"time":446143,"text":"then you often get the shivers,"},{"time":448443,"text":"because of how little\nwe expect of each other,"},{"time":450795,"text":"of how little we actually\nseem to expect of our life,"},{"time":454709,"text":"and what the good life looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457850,"text":"So that's a fourth question\nI'd like to leave you with:"},{"time":460897,"text":"What vision of the good life\ndo your designs convey?"},{"time":465989,"text":"And speaking of design,"},{"time":467385,"text":"you'll notice that I already\nbroadened the discussion,"},{"time":471599,"text":"because it's not just persuasive\ntechnology that we're talking about here,"},{"time":476067,"text":"it's any piece of design\nthat we put out here in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480168,"text":"I don't know whether you know"},{"time":481592,"text":"the great communication researcher\nPaul Watzlawick who, back in the '60s,"},{"time":485171,"text":"made the argument\nthat we cannot not communicate."},{"time":487706,"text":"Even if we choose to be silent,\nwe chose to be silent,"},{"time":490331,"text":"and we're communicating something\nby choosing to be silent."},{"time":493311,"text":"And in the same way\nthat we cannot not communicate,"},{"time":496070,"text":"we cannot not persuade:"},{"time":497625,"text":"whatever we do or refrain from doing,"},{"time":499660,"text":"whatever we put out there\nas a piece of design, into the world,"},{"time":504049,"text":"has a persuasive component."},{"time":506120,"text":"It tries to affect people."},{"time":508017,"text":"It puts a certain vision of the good life\nout there in front of us,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511788,"text":"which is what Peter-Paul Verbeek,"},{"time":513437,"text":"the Dutch philosopher of technology, says."},{"time":516177,"text":"No matter whether we as designers\nintend it or not,"},{"time":520149,"text":"we materialize morality."},{"time":522315,"text":"We make certain things\nharder and easier to do."},{"time":525142,"text":"We organize the existence of people."},{"time":527377,"text":"We put a certain vision"},{"time":528552,"text":"of what good or bad or normal or usual is"},{"time":531980,"text":"in front of people,"},{"time":533155,"text":"by everything we put\nout there in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535987,"text":"Even something as innocuous\nas a set of school chairs"},{"time":539097,"text":"is a persuasive technology,"},{"time":541168,"text":"because it presents and materializes\na certain vision of the good life --"},{"time":545882,"text":"a good life in which teaching\nand learning and listening"},{"time":548763,"text":"is about one person teaching,\nthe others listening;"},{"time":551886,"text":"in which it is about\nlearning-is-done-while-sitting;"},{"time":555963,"text":"in which you learn for yourself;"},{"time":557582,"text":"in which you're not supposed\nto change these rules,"},{"time":560026,"text":"because the chairs\nare fixed to the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563628,"text":"And even something as innocuous\nas a single-design chair,"},{"time":566563,"text":"like this one by Arne Jacobsen,"},{"time":568159,"text":"is a persuasive technology,"},{"time":569959,"text":"because, again, it communicates\nan idea of the good life:"},{"time":573475,"text":"a good life -- a life that you,\nas a designer, consent to by saying,"},{"time":578424,"text":"\"In a good life, goods are produced\nas sustainably or unsustainably"},{"time":581955,"text":"as this chair."},{"time":583590,"text":"Workers are treated as well or as badly"},{"time":585591,"text":"as the workers were treated\nthat built that chair.\""},{"time":588502,"text":"The good life is a life\nwhere design is important"},{"time":590827,"text":"because somebody obviously took\nthe time and spent the money"},{"time":593772,"text":"for that kind of well-designed chair;"},{"time":595580,"text":"where tradition is important,"},{"time":597008,"text":"because this is a traditional classic\nand someone cared about this;"},{"time":600198,"text":"and where there is something\nas conspicuous consumption,"},{"time":602912,"text":"where it is OK and normal to spend\na humongous amount of money"},{"time":605892,"text":"on such a chair,"},{"time":607067,"text":"to signal to other people\nwhat your social status is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609664,"text":"So these are the kinds of layers,\nthe kinds of questions"},{"time":613005,"text":"I wanted to lead you through today;"},{"time":614999,"text":"the question of: What are the intentions\nthat you bring to bear"},{"time":618057,"text":"when you're designing something?"},{"time":619641,"text":"What are the effects, intended\nand unintended, that you're having?"},{"time":622917,"text":"What are the values\nyou're using to judge those?"},{"time":625742,"text":"What are the virtues, the aspirations"},{"time":627739,"text":"that you're actually expressing in that?"},{"time":630140,"text":"And how does that apply,"},{"time":632021,"text":"not just to persuasive technology,"},{"time":634031,"text":"but to everything you design?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636652,"text":"Do we stop there?"},{"time":638555,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":640031,"text":"I think that all of these things\nare eventually informed"},{"time":644493,"text":"by the core of all of this,"},{"time":645940,"text":"and this is nothing but life itself."},{"time":649334,"text":"Why, when the question\nof what the good life is"},{"time":652075,"text":"informs everything that we design,"},{"time":654438,"text":"should we stop at design\nand not ask ourselves:"},{"time":657256,"text":"How does it apply to our own life?"},{"time":659621,"text":"\"Why should the lamp\nor the house be an art object,"},{"time":662357,"text":"but not our life?\""},{"time":663557,"text":"as Michel Foucault puts it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665436,"text":"Just to give you a practical\nexample of Buster Benson."},{"time":669071,"text":"This is Buster setting up\na pull-up machine"},{"time":671353,"text":"at the office of his new\nstart-up, Habit Labs,"},{"time":673989,"text":"where they're trying to build\nother applications like \"Health Month\""},{"time":677228,"text":"for people."},{"time":678410,"text":"And why is he building a thing like this?"},{"time":680396,"text":"Well, here is the set of axioms"},{"time":682453,"text":"that Habit Labs, Buster's start-up,\nput up for themselves"},{"time":685875,"text":"on how they wanted to work\ntogether as a team"},{"time":688604,"text":"when they're building\nthese applications --"},{"time":690657,"text":"a set of moral principles\nthey set themselves"},{"time":692870,"text":"for working together --"},{"time":694255,"text":"one of them being,"},{"time":695517,"text":"\"We take care of our own health\nand manage our own burnout.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":698961,"text":"Because ultimately,\nhow can you ask yourselves"},{"time":702485,"text":"and how can you find an answer\non what vision of the good life"},{"time":706439,"text":"you want to convey and create\nwith your designs"},{"time":709632,"text":"without asking the question:"},{"time":711386,"text":"What vision of the good life\ndo you yourself want to live?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":715758,"text":"And with that,"},{"time":717685,"text":"I thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719121,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}